      "inheritance_hierarchy": "Kernel.sol defines KernelAdapter -> {Policy, Module}. Policies: Create (Policy, Signer, Zone, Accumulator), Stop (Policy, Signer, Reclaimer, Accumulator), Guard (Policy, BaseGuard), Factory (Policy), Admin (Policy). Modules: Storage (Proxiable, Module, StorageBase), PaymentEscrow (Proxiable, Module, PaymentEscrowBase). Packages: Signer (EIP-712 helpers), Accumulator (memory struct accumulator), Reclaimer (delegatecall-only reclaim function).",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "OpenZeppelin ECDSA (signature recovery)",
        "OpenZeppelin IERC20/IERC721/IERC1155 interfaces",
        "Gnosis Safe contracts: SafeL2, SafeProxyFactory, BaseGuard/GuardManager, Enum, TokenCallbackHandler",
        "Seaport types/core: ZoneParameters, SpentItem, ReceivedItem and Zone interface expectations",
        "Solady LibString (panic code formatting)"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "Custom ERC-1822/UUPS-like pattern via Proxiable base (not provided here) used by Storage and PaymentEscrow. Both modules are intended to be used behind a proxy (onlyByProxy) and include MODULE_PROXY_INSTANTIATION initializer guarded by onlyUninitialized. Kernel supports module upgrade by swapping module address for a keycode; Proxiable supports implementation upgrade within a proxy (upgrade/freeze). No Diamond pattern detected.",
      "access_control_structure": "Centralized Kernel-based role system (Kernel.hasRole) used by Policy.onlyRole for user-facing privileged entrypoints. Module methods use Module.permissioned() to restrict calls to Kernel-activated policies with explicit selector permissions. Kernel.executor controls module/policy lifecycle via executeAction; Kernel.admin controls roles via grantRole/revokeRole. Guard also enforces runtime restrictions on Safe-originating transactions based on Storage state and whitelists."
    },
